<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-10-0561 </DOCNO><TEXT>Several resolution functions are analysed for description of the unsharpnessof knife-edge images. The comparisons are done regarding the definitionof unsharpness by Klasens resp. by Morgan. The suitability of a resolutionfunction is assessed according to the goodness of the data fit to themeasured densities. The investigations are applied to Dy transfer method,track etch technique and Gd direct method, in each case distinguishingbetween inherent and geometrical unsharpness. (orig.) With 14 figs.,7 tabs.</TEXT></DOC>